The fusion of the cyclohexane ring provides additional rigidity and introduces strain in the molecule which tends to increase the melting point. However, the saturated nature of the cyclohexane may offset some of that increase due to lack of pi-stacking interactions present in fully aromatic systems. The introduction of each saturated ring typically raises the melting point by a few degrees due to increased molecular complexity and slight changes in packing efficiency.
